I&#x27;ve encountered engineers who takes things too literally for this to work:<p>Me: &quot;should this be documented in the team wiki?&quot;
Engineer: &quot;Probably&quot;
&quot;should we document it now before we forget?&quot;
&quot;Okay&quot;
&quot;um, do you want to do it? I could do it for you after I&#x27;m done with my tasks if you need help&quot;
&quot;okay, you do it&quot;<p><i>whoosh</i> hint not taken. It&#x27;s not rare either since the stereotype of socially awkward literal engineers is not entirely undeserved.
